Putting together a Christmas table was a cinch thanks to the Festive Set from @thesoupspoonsg. The spread of goodies that you're looking at is from the "Peace Set" ($299), serving up to 10 and comprises of seven mains and sides next to two soups of your choice:

‚ùÑÔ∏è "Lobster Bits-que" soup and the Christmas edition of Soup Spoon's french onions soup was my pick.
‚ùÑÔ∏è Sourdough Foccacia
‚ùÑÔ∏è Boccocino Cheese Skewers
‚ùÑÔ∏è Shepherd‚Äôs Pie
‚ùÑÔ∏è Truffle Mac & Cheese
‚ùÑÔ∏è Festive Roast Chicken with Stuffing + Yorkshire Pudding
‚ùÑÔ∏è Basque-style Burnt Cheesecake

What I liked about the curated set is that it arrived warm and toasty in a large thermal carrier, accompanied by two neat parcels of 'Decorate-It-Yourself Cheesecake Kit' and 'Festive Merry Kit' that includes an assortment of merrymaking supplies to jazz up the table. They're pretty much party-ready.

Menu-wise, the stuffed roast chicken (2.5kg), truffle mac & cheese, and sourdough Foccacia (1.5kg) received the most fanfare, with the latter two garnering an even better reception after a quick tour in the oven.

Dressing up the naked Basque-style Burnt Cheesecake (1.2kg) proved to be another winner and I can imagine it to be a fun ice-breaking activity for both kids and adults, using the Christmas condiments, and cake toppers provided. If you're up for a bit of cake decorating contest, Soup Spoon is giving a $100 gift card for the "Best Decorated Cheesecake" -- more info at their page @thesoupspoonsg

Eagle Wings Loft's rendition of the luxurious Lobster Risotto ($38) dish ticks all the boxes, hosting chunks of sweet, supple lobster meat, scallops, prawn, pops of briny tobiko, and bits of sauteed garlic all held in the creamy, luscious folds of the wonderfully textured risotto rice. 

It's no doubt the main attraction at this nautical-themed casual diner that also serves up another of my favorite in the form of juicy pomelo salad ($12, pic 5). A mix of pomelo, pomegranate, grapefruit, cherry tomato, lettuce, poached prawns, and Sakura Ebi tossed in a sweet chili lime dressing before topping with roasted chopped peanut and pork floss, resulting in an appetizing combination of crunchy textures and refreshing flavors.

Truffle oil-infused Wild Mushroom Soup ($8, pic 4) occupies the richer-tasting spectrum of the diner's menu, as was the Bacon & Egg Wagyu Burger ($18, pic 2, 3). Both dishes deliver on taste and provide relatively good value for money. Bacon, egg, and melted cheese did their job of amping-up the heartiness of my choice of medium-rare chargrilled Australian wagyu patty on toasted brioche buns.

Elsewhere on the menu: Coral Rush ($9, pic 6), a mocktail capped by a striking purple cloud of cotton candy that's meant to be dissolved by the accompanying soda. Desserts came from neighbor @acaiguru.sg. The Acai Guru Bowls ($6.50 for small, pic 7, 8)  are essentially layered acai berry puree and frozen yogurt topped with an assortment of nuts, seeds, and fruits that works splendidly as a wholesome treat.

There's a newly opened Indian restaurant at the indoor stadium that dishes out some of the most succulent tandoori Lamb Chops ($21, 2nd pic) that are imbued with a distinctive hit of tandoor smoke and littered with plenty of delightful cragged exterior. Biting into the Kanpuri-marinated meaty parts with the juicy, char-bits-encrusted rendered lamb fat was especially gratifying, and it didn't need much of that accompanying ' chili crab' style sauce at all. 

Grilled Saffron Tandoori Prawns (with spiced Indian slaw, $23) and Paneer Tikka ($18, pic 3) made up the two other tandoor dishes we had. The former packs a satisfying crunch and a robust marinade on the smoky crustacean, while the latter was marinated cubes of chewy tandoor-grilled cottage cheese, meant to be eaten with refreshing lime yogurt and onion radish salad sandwiched in between. It's a first-of-its-kind type of cheese delivery system for me, and I was informed that it's how it's consumed on the streets of India. 

The Daab Chingri ($26) that you see in the first picture originated from the eastern coast of India, and it's otherwise known as prawns slow-cooked in a coconut shell. Being simmered in coconut paste, it has similarities with the rich, creamy Thai green curry that we're familiar with (they share the same Bay of Bengali, after all). However, this variant boasts a notable mustard quality to it, giving it a savory-earthy edge and making it exceedingly moreish with rice or naan. Just look at the gravy's consistency and how beautifully it clings to the prawn. If only there were more than three prawns within the tender coconut.

FYI, @Yarana.sg currently occupies the space that Myra's was. At the time of my visit, they were in the process of developing bottled cocktail made from a vintage cast iron soda-making machine that hails from the street vendors of India. Check it out in picture 6.

If you miss traveling to Japan, visit the Ibaraki fair @isetansg Scotts from now till 31 March 2022.

Home to the Pacific Ocean, mountains, countless rivers and expansive lakes, Ibaraki features an ever-changing array of unique landscapes just waiting to be explored. The rich natural environment means there's plenty of fresh, local cuisine to sample wherever you go in Ibaraki.

The last night in Paris called for a proper Paris Brest and Brasserie Dubillot does not disappoint. It‚Äôs not about the p√¢te √† choux, nor the generous lashings of chocolate sauce but the crunch of hazelnuts roasted over what I assume to be a charcoal fire judging by the gentle arabesque of smoke that sometimes escape from the kitchens. These hazelnuts were just a shade shy of being burnt, lending the entire dish a sophisticated bitter lift. This for me is how you slingshot a rustic french dessert invented in 1910 well into 2022 ‚Äî and beyond.

Why have one croissant from @dupainpourdemain, awarded the best boulangerie in France for 2019 when you can have six? I mean it‚Äôs not like it‚Äôs the most accessible spot for travellers. Was it too much? Maybe. Did I have any regrets? Hell no.

I don‚Äôt have high hopes for a better 2022, and for all we know, the world may rip itself into shreds. So for me at least, I‚Äôve come to realise how important it is to find the things that you hold most dear, and to nourish it, and cherish it, for it in turn will nourish you. For what it‚Äôs worth, 2021 has shown that it‚Äôs possible to live with grace amidst chaos. And if that‚Äôs all I can do as we await the next chapter in the history of humanity, then I‚Äôd say it‚Äôs a life well lived.

So my former editor @tommywee sent me some of his wife‚Äôs granola that he‚Äôs been raving about for at least half a decade, and it‚Äôs every bit as delicious as I imagined. The blackout chocolate is deep, dark and bittersweet with whole pecans and slivers of almonds that made eating it a real joy. @kongpowkitty, you‚Äôve got a winner in your hands. I know a lot of heart has gone into it so thank you so much for sharing it with me.

[Did you know] that Bak kwa (ËÇâÂπ≤) is a delicacy that is said to have originated from Fujian province in China, where the people were poor and where meat was a festive treat reserved for Chinese New Year. To make the treat last longer, the pork was sliced thinly, marinated with sugar and spices, air-dried and cooked over a hot plate.

The delicacy subsequently made its way to Singapore, where the pork slices are usually air-dried, then grilled over charcoal for a sweet and smoky flavour. Beyond being tasty, bak kwa is also called ‚Äúlong yoke‚Äù in Cantonese, which means to have good fortune.

With silky threads of Chinese la mian, expect bowls of noodles that seek to delight and surprise with two of their specialty broths ‚Äì shrimp broth with flawless union of fresh sea prawns, pork bones and Chinese spices, & tonkotsu broth with its rich and creamy collagen texture after long hours of simmering with pork bones.

Highlight would definitely be their specialty dish ‚Äì ü¶êLe Signature Trio Shrimp Ramen ($19.90) served with big sea prawns, prawn dumplings and handmade ebiko prawn paste balls. The big juicy prawns here are all farmed from local fisheries in order to go through sedulous selection to produce the umami palatable flavours and tangerine-orange. The result is a rich flavoursome broth that is bound to satisfy your noodle cravings anytime any day üòª

Other selection include Big Prawns & Braised Pork Rib Shrimp Ramen ($17.90), Ebiko Prawn Paste Shrimp Ramen ($14.90) and more. Don‚Äôt forget to add on their inexpensive side dishes such as the Seasoned Bamboo Shoots, Chilled Crunchy Cucumber, Braised Beancurd in Tonkotsu Broth, Chilled Silken Tofu with Century Egg, Long Jing Tea Lava Eggs, Braised Pork Ribs with Scallions and Crispy Chicken Cutlet. (Swipe for menu).
.

5 things I like about our staycation at Ascott Orchard Serviced Suites ‚ù§

„ÄäWelcome Gift„Äã sets me in a good mood and the masks they provided came in handy when I realised I forgot to bring extra masks for Day 2 to 4.

„ÄäWasher/Dryer„Äã is a godsend! One downside of staycation is the amount of laundry you have to do at home when staycation ends. Not a problem if you can wash and dry them daily (for free) during the staycation like us though!

„ÄäFully Functional Kitchen„Äã with huge fridge, utensils, pots, knives and plates makes it convenient for me to cut fruits for my little one. Most of the time we also eat too little fruits during staycation too but this staycay, we ate fruits twice each day. Parents with younger children (or children with allergy) will like that they can prepare almost any meal for their children.

„ÄäFull Size Dining Table„Äãso our family of 5 can eat comfortably in our room when we don't feel like dining out. This is the kind of room service I love!

„ÄäConvenient Location„Äã made it easy for us to see the CNY decor at Chinatown, get to the duck tours and take many many electric buses and 3 doors buses. We are also surrounded by many malls, making it easier to bring 1 kid and 2 oldies out for meals and shopping.

Actually their service is also commendable! Especially housekeeping and the guys at lift lobby!

What about you? Which hotel/serviced suites gets your vote? Anyone going for a staycation next week during the School Holidays?

We love Pano Kato.

Pano Kato is Greek for upstairs and downstairs, referring to House of AnLi's store¬†& bistro upstairs and Pano Kato downstairs in Tanglin Mall.

We love the airy, spacious restaurant and the simple but delicious Mediterranean food it serves. We've not been disappointed by any dishes tried here so far. Even salads and roasted veggies are done really well.

Pity they are always short of staff on Sat afternoons, with 2-3 staff serving an almost full restaurant. When you do get the attention of the busy staff, they are attentive and offer good service but the problem is getting their attention. Expect to wait at the entrance (even if you have reservations) and any mid meal requests. Once food is ordered, service is prompt though so I'm guessing there are more staff in the kitchen.

If you can take it slow, it is nice to dine here. Eachern loves their pizza very very much so we will become regulars.

BBQ Ribs Recipe.

Ingredients:

2pcs Baby back ribs, rack of 5/6 ribs.

Dry rub:
1 tbsp Salt
1 tbsp White pepper
2 tsp 5 spice powder
1 tbsp chilli powder
2 tbsps Garlic powder

Gochujang glaze:
2 tbsps Gochujang
1tbsp Rice vinegar
2 tbsps Honey
1 tsp Salt
1 tbsp Sugar
1 tbsp Sesame oil
2 tsps Fish sauce

sliced spring onions (garnish)

Method:

1) Remove membrane of baby back ribs, prep into portions that can fit into air fryer
2) Mix dry rub
3) Massage in a generously amount of dry rubs onto the ribs
4) Wrap ribs tightly with aluminum foil
5) Air-fry at 160C for 2.5 - 3 hours
6) Combine gochujang glaze and brush on ribs while it‚Äôs still hot
7) Air-fry at 200C for 6 mins, uncovered

Kra Pow Gai (Thai Basil Chicken) recipe:

Ingredients:

500g minced chicken

2pcs small red chillies, chopped
2pcs small green chillies, chopped

1tbsp minced garlic

2tsp light soya sauce
1tsp dark soya sauce
2tsp fish sauce
1tbsp oyster sauce

20-25 pcs holy basil 

Method:

1) Fry chilies and garlic in oil
2) Add minced chicken
3) Season with light soya sauce, dark soya sauce, fish sauce and oyster sauce
4) Turn off the flame, add holy basil and stir-fry
5) Serve with white rice and a crispy fried egg

Chilli Oil Noodles Recipe:

Ingredients:

3 cups peanut oil
300g chilli flakes
50g ginger
1 whole garlic
2 bunch spring onions

1pcs cinnamon stick
¬Ω pcs star anise
7pcs bay leaves
1 tbsp numbing peppercorns
1 tbsp coriander seeds

Knife-cut noodles
1 tbsp soya sauce
1 tsp black vinegar
1 tsp dark soya sauce

Sesame seeds (garnish)
Finely chopped spring onions (garnish)

Method:

1) Heat peanut oil at medium low to low heat. 
2) Fry spring onions, garlic and ginger until golden brown and wilted. Go as low and slow as you can to infuse the most flavour.
3) Add cinnamon, star anise, bay leaves, numbing peppercorns and coriander seeds. Control oil temperature to avoid burning. 
4) Drain oil and pour into chilli flakes.
5) Season oil with salt and sugar.
6) Set aside and allow to cool. 

7) Blanch noodles. 
8) Add light soya sauce, black vinegar, dark soya sauce and homemade chilli oil into a bowl. 
9) Combine with noodles
10) Garnish with sesame seeds and finely chopped spring onions.

Garlic Prawns recipe:

Ingredients:

14 pcs prawns, deshelled and deveined

1tsp Salt
1 tbsp Black pepper
2 tbsps salted butter
2 tbsp Paprika
1 garlic
1 tbsp ground thyme

Olive oil

Lemon 
Spring onions

Method

1) Cut top off garlic, drizzle olive oil, add salt and pepper and air fry at 190C for 40minutes
2) Deshell and devein prawns
3) Add butter, black pepper, paprika, ground thyme and roasted garlic into a bowl. Mix until thoroughly combined.
4) Toss prawn in mixture
5) Air fry 200C 5mins. Flip and then 3 more minutes.
6) Garnish with lemon wedges and chopped italian parsley.

Kung Pao Chicken recipe

Ingredients:

600g boneless skinless chicken thighs

Marinade:
3 tbsp chinese cooking wine (liao jiu)
1 tsp salt
1 tbsp soya sauce
1 tbsp dark soy sauce
1 tbsp cornstarch
2 tbsp oil

Sauce:
1 tbsp cooking wine (liao jiu)
1 tsp light soya sauce
2 tsp dark soya sauce
1 tsp MSG
1 tsp cornstarch
¬Ω tbsp oyster sauce

10 pcs dried chillies, cut
10g ginger, chopped
10g garlic, chopped

3 stalks spring onions, cut into 3cm strips
¬Ω cup peanuts

Method:

1) Cut and marinate chicken for 30 minutes.
2) Fry chicken and set aside
3) Combine sauce
4) Fry dried chillies, garlic and ginger until fragrant
5) Add chicken back in
6) Add sauce
7) Stir-fry and coat evenly
8) Add spring onions and peanuts, toss. 
9) Serve with white rice.

Reposted from @vegangotgame - üòç CRISPY OVEN BAKED SPINACH TACOS! üì∑ by @elavegan üö®üö®via @vegangotgame #vegangotgame @taquilhosoficiall
Recipe: Servings- 9
9 small spinach tortillas (5-inch diameter)
2 cups of cooked rice (360 g)
One 15 oz can kidney beans or black beans (rinsed and drained)
1 small/medium onion
1/2 tbsp oil
2 garlic cloves
1/2 bell pepper
3/4 cup canned mushrooms (100 g) or use fresh
Spice mix: 1/2 tsp onion powder, 1/2 tsp ground cumin, 1/2 tsp paprika, 1/4 tsp smoked paprika, 1/4 tsp ground ginger, 1/4 tsp black pepper (or more to taste), sea salt to taste
1 tbsp balsamic vinegar
1 tbsp soy sauce (gluten-free if needed)
4 tbsp plant-based milk
1/3 cup passata
2 tbsp hot sauce (or use less/more to taste)
1 batch vegan cheese sauce

Instructions
Cook rice as per the instructions on the package. You will need 2 cups of cooked rice for this recipe.
Prepare Ela's spinach tortillas. Or use store-bought flour tortillas or corn tortillas of choice.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a pan/skillet over medium heat and add the onion, mushrooms, and bell pepper.
Saut√© for about 3-5 minutes, then add garlic for a further minute. Stir occasionally.
Add all spices, balsamic vinegar, soy sauce, plant-based milk, passata, and hot sauce. Stir and let simmer for about 3 minutes.
Add cooked rice and beans, stir and turn off the heat.
Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.
Preheat oven to 410 degrees Fahrenheit (210 degrees Celsius) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Make one batch of the vegan cheese sauce (click) or use store-bought vegan cheese.
Add about 2 tbsp of the rice filling on one side of a tortilla and 1 tbsp of the vegan cheese. Fold the other side over the filling and press it slightly down with your fingers. Do the same for the remaining tortillas.
Transfer all tortillas onto the baking sheet. Bake in the oven for about 10-15 minutes or until crispy. Enjoy hot! - #regrann

Britney Spears, Conservatorship versus Deputyship, and YOU!
-- Continue in comments

(1)

Britney is now free! 

The US Congress found this piece of news important enough to invite Britney to share her experience with them. She has yet to decide on the invitation. 

But Britney is free from what?
"Conservatorship." What's that? 

Is this just a US thing? No. Are there any implications for me? Yes. Let's consider that at the end. 

1. US Conservatorship and Britney 

Courts in the United States can grant Conservatorship over individuals who are unable to make their own decisions. This can arise when individuals have dementia or other illnesses that affect their mental capacity. 

In 2007, after Britney's divorce from Kevin Federline and the loss of custody over her children, Britney became erratic in her behaviour. Her mental health became an issue. Among various things, there was a stand-off when she allegedly did not want to hand over custody of her two sons. In 2008, following psychiatric assessment, she was admitted to hospital twice. 

In view of Britney's public mental health crisis, a Conservatorship (like a legal guardianship) was set up in 2008. Her father, Jamie Spears, applied to the US Court for the Conservatorship and was appointed the Conservator. 

As a result, the father controlled many aspects of Britney's finances and personal life for 13 years. 

Such Conservatorship covers two key areas of a person's life:
‚Ä¢ Estate and financial affairs, and
‚Ä¢ Personal welfare. 

So, the father had power over Britney's finances, career decisions, and major personal matters. This included matters like visits with her teenage sons and whether she can remarry. 

In 2019, Jamie Spears had asked to step down as Conservator with regards to Britney's personal welfare. He cited health reasons, and the Court appointed a professional as replacement.
